tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The laboratory results show a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.9%), indicating prediabetes, while fasting glucose is within normal limits. Renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are all within normal ranges. No acute abnormalities detected; recommend monitoring glycemic status and considering lifestyle modifications to prevent progression to diabetes.
